The Accessablility implications of the smart home are actually very positive, smart homes provide a very simple way to interact with houseing,
this could be able to help some people with disabilities, providing a simple way to interact with their homes features while also allowing 
for automation of trivial tasks that might face disabled people with challenges.

the possibility of simplisity for the user allows for the accessibility of smart homes to be very understandable, convenient and approachable
for everyone that wants to buy either a newly built smart home, or to install new technology to their current home.
